The paper discusses the science of measuring AI systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of crowd-sourced datasets as instruments for measuring AI performance, which relates to machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of word similarity benchmarks, which relates to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
